01:08:22,070 --> 01:08:24,010
And, uh,
bring the old guitar.

1248
01:08:24,050 --> 01:08:26,150
Yeah, soon.
Promise.

1249
01:08:28,200 --> 01:08:30,210
Merry Christmas, John.
Merry Christmas.

1250
01:08:35,210 --> 01:08:38,120
(Linda) Being mobbed
by fans and journalists
in Tokyo

1251
01:08:38,160 --> 01:08:41,120
at the start of
the wings world tour
was a nightmare.

1252
01:08:41,160 --> 01:08:44,110
We had our kids with US
including baby James

1253
01:08:44,150 --> 01:08:47,170
and thought a quiet
vip. Entrance
had been arranged.

1254
01:08:47,210 --> 01:08:49,130
[People chattering]

1255
01:08:53,080 --> 01:08:55,180
(Man) Mr. McCartney,
picture.

1256
01:08:55,220 --> 01:08:57,160
Hey, you take him. Here.

1257
01:08:59,140 --> 01:09:01,000
[Photographers clamoring]

1258
01:09:01,040 --> 01:09:02,200
How's it going?

1259
01:09:04,160 --> 01:09:05,220
(Paul) Hey, big guy.

1260
01:09:11,230 --> 01:09:13,100
Oh, great.

1261
01:09:13,230 --> 01:09:15,110
Wonderful.

1262
01:09:19,050 --> 01:09:20,060
Mr. McCartney.

1263
01:09:20,100 --> 01:09:21,170
Hang on. Listen,
this is a mistake.

1264
01:09:21,210 --> 01:09:22,200
[Speaking in Japanese]

1265
01:09:23,000 --> 01:09:24,130
Hang on. Listen.
Listen, mate.

1266
01:09:24,170 --> 01:09:27,030
This is a-- it's a mistake.
It's just a mistake.

1267
01:09:29,220 --> 01:09:34,150
Mr. McCartney.
Mr. McCartney,
you're under arrest.

1268
01:09:34,190 --> 01:09:37,110
(Linda) Where are
you taking him? No. Paul.

1269
01:09:37,150 --> 01:09:38,200
Hey, come on.

1270
01:09:39,000 --> 01:09:40,180
Lin, just keep an eye
on the kids.

1271
01:09:41,130 --> 01:09:42,230
You come with me both.

1272
01:09:44,160 --> 01:09:45,180
The hotel, please.

1273
01:09:45,220 --> 01:09:47,070
It's fine. It's fine.

1274
01:09:47,110 --> 01:09:48,210
[Speaking in Japanese]

1275
01:09:52,230 --> 01:09:54,170
(Stella) Mummy,
it's on again.

1276
01:09:58,110 --> 01:10:00,010
[James whimpering]

1277
01:10:00,050 --> 01:10:01,100
(Linda) It's ok.

1278
01:10:02,080 --> 01:10:04,080
What's going to
happen to him?

1279
01:10:04,120 --> 01:10:07,100
I don't know, darling.
They'll probably
keep him overnight.

1280
01:10:07,140 --> 01:10:09,200
Release him with a fine.

1281
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:12,220
Keep him where?
I don't know.

1282
01:10:14,180 --> 01:10:16,060
I don't know.

1283
01:10:20,000 --> 01:10:21,190
[Cell door opening]

1284
01:10:24,150 --> 01:10:25,220
[Speaking in Japanese]

1285
01:10:27,040 --> 01:10:28,190
Mr. McCartney.

1286
01:10:28,230 --> 01:10:31,170
Dolan Warren knott,
British vice council.

1287
01:10:31,210 --> 01:10:33,230
Very pleased to meet you.

1288
01:10:39,230 --> 01:10:41,220
Linda must be
frantic, eh?

1289
01:10:43,190 --> 01:10:47,110
Look, we haven't spent
a single night apart,
you know?

1290
01:10:47,150 --> 01:10:51,150
So, uh, how long before
you can get me out of here?

1291
01:10:51,190 --> 01:10:54,130
I'm afraid it's not
quite so easy,
Mr. McCartney.

1292
01:10:54,170 --> 01:10:56,190
The Japanese are
a rather
conservative lot

1293
01:10:56,230 --> 01:10:58,150
on matters
such as drugs.

1294
01:10:58,190 --> 01:11:00,150
By violating their laws,

1295
01:11:00,190 --> 01:11:02,120
you've shown disrespect
to Japan is
the way they see it.

1296
01:11:02,160 --> 01:11:04,160
No. No. No.
No disrespect.
No disrespect.

1297
01:11:04,200 --> 01:11:07,090
I just--
I just didn't think,
that's all.

1298
01:11:08,090 --> 01:11:09,190
Well, there's a chap
in here

1299
01:11:09,230 --> 01:11:12,060
who was caught
with much less
marijuana than you,

1300
01:11:12,100 --> 01:11:14,150
and he's been locked up
for 3 months already.

1301
01:11:14,190 --> 01:11:16,140
They could give
you eight years.

1302
01:11:16,180 --> 01:11:17,210
Eight-- eight years?

1303
01:11:21,050 --> 01:11:22,140
Oh.

1304
01:11:22,180 --> 01:11:24,010
That's barbaric.

1305
01:11:24,050 --> 01:11:26,050
Yes. But there it is.

1306
01:11:28,050 --> 01:11:31,120
Look, it's past midnight.
I'll visit with your wife
in the morning.

1307
01:11:31,160 --> 01:11:33,130
Rest assured,
Mr. McCartney,

1308
01:11:33,170 --> 01:11:35,220
we shall do
everything we can.

1309
01:11:47,200 --> 01:11:48,220
[Cell door opening]

1310
01:11:49,230 --> 01:11:51,010
Lin. Lin.

1311
01:11:51,050 --> 01:11:52,060
Hi.

1312
01:11:52,100 --> 01:11:53,180
[Sighing]

1313
01:11:55,150 --> 01:11:57,210
Six days feels
more like six months.

1314
01:12:02,070 --> 01:12:05,030
Oh, how are the kids?

1315
01:12:05,070 --> 01:12:07,200
Worried, but we're ok.

1316
01:12:08,000 --> 01:12:09,170
The band left
once they realized

1317
01:12:09,210 --> 01:12:13,000
that there was no way
to save the tour, but...

1318
01:12:13,040 --> 01:12:14,210
Well, they're not happy.

1319
01:12:16,020 --> 01:12:20,110
Oh, it was
so incredibly dumb.

1320
01:12:20,150 --> 01:12:22,140
[Laughing]
I know.

1321
01:12:25,200 --> 01:12:28,010
[Reporter speaking
in Japanese]

1322
01:12:28,220 --> 01:12:30,110
[Crowd cheering]

1323
01:12:38,220 --> 01:12:40,130
[Chattering]

1324
01:12:53,120 --> 01:12:55,040
(Linda) I've had it
with touring.

1325
01:12:55,080 --> 01:12:57,090
10 years of packing
and unpacking.

1326
01:12:57,130 --> 01:12:59,020
Hauling the kids
all around the world.

1327
01:12:59,060 --> 01:13:01,150
Living out of hotels.
I'm tired.

1328
01:13:01,190 --> 01:13:03,090
Tokyo was rough.

1329
01:13:03,130 --> 01:13:04,230
It was tougher on you
than on me.

1330
01:13:05,030 --> 01:13:07,110
I promise it won't
happen again.

1331
01:13:07,150 --> 01:13:09,100
No. No more touring.

1332
01:13:09,140 --> 01:13:11,080
Promise me that.
Lin, I can't.

1333
01:13:11,120 --> 01:13:13,170
Stepping up in front
of an audience is my life.

1334
01:13:13,210 --> 01:13:15,180
What about my life?

1335
01:13:15,220 --> 01:13:18,100
All right. I'm sorry.
Our life.

1336
01:13:18,140 --> 01:13:22,020
There are other things
that I want to do.

1337
01:13:22,060 --> 01:13:23,210
Like your photography
book. Great.

1338
01:13:24,010 --> 01:13:26,190
My photography book.
My vegetarian cookbook.

1339
01:13:26,230 --> 01:13:28,220
We're always saying
that people
in our position

1340
01:13:29,020 --> 01:13:30,030
should make a difference,

1341
01:13:30,070 --> 01:13:32,080
so let's do more
for animal rights.

1342
01:13:34,110 --> 01:13:38,010
And we should
spend more time at home
with our family.

1343
01:13:43,150 --> 01:13:44,150
[Chuckling]

1344
01:13:47,110 --> 01:13:49,060
Be safe. Be warm.

1345
01:13:49,100 --> 01:13:50,160
Love you.

1346
01:13:52,030 --> 01:13:54,000
Thank you so much.

1347
01:13:54,040 --> 01:13:55,080
Bye, mummy.
Bye, baby.

1348
01:14:02,200 --> 01:14:04,010
[Bird squawking]

1349
01:14:13,170 --> 01:14:15,000
What's wrong?

1350
01:14:18,080 --> 01:14:20,160
John's dead.

1351
01:14:20,200 --> 01:14:23,190
(Male reporter) The news
of John Lennon's death
has stunned the world.

1352
01:14:23,230 --> 01:14:25,140
Fans keep
a constant vigil

1353
01:14:25,180 --> 01:14:27,230
outside the Dakota apartments
in New York City

1354
01:14:28,030 --> 01:14:29,200
where he was
shot last night.

1355
01:14:30,000 --> 01:14:32,110
Whenever-- whenever anyone
I love dies,

1356
01:14:32,150 --> 01:14:34,200
I never get a chance
to say goodbye.

1357
01:14:35,000 --> 01:14:37,050
...as soon as the word
was made public.

1358
01:14:37,090 --> 01:14:40,050
Most say they just want
to be near the place
where this icon...

1359
01:14:40,220 --> 01:14:41,210
Mum.

1360
01:14:42,010 --> 01:14:43,150
...was gunned down.

1361
01:14:44,080 --> 01:14:45,210
Now John.

1362
01:14:49,230 --> 01:14:53,140
Poor yoko and Sean.

1363
01:14:55,060 --> 01:14:57,130
Will he even remember
his daddy?

1364
01:14:57,170 --> 01:15:00,040
Oh, he'll never
forget John.

1365
01:15:03,060 --> 01:15:05,100
No one will ever
forget John.

1366
01:15:09,190 --> 01:15:11,020
Oh, god.

1367
01:15:11,060 --> 01:15:12,220
Oh, god.

1368
01:15:17,170 --> 01:15:19,080
[Dog barking]

1369
01:15:27,090 --> 01:15:28,190
[Creaking]

1370
01:15:29,100 --> 01:15:30,190
[Moans]

1371
01:15:50,080 --> 01:15:52,120
Oh, sorry, love.
Did I wake you?

1372
01:15:52,160 --> 01:15:54,060
No.

1373
01:15:54,100 --> 01:15:57,020
I had another nightmare.
Oh.

1374
01:16:00,040 --> 01:16:01,100
[Sighing]

1375
01:16:01,140 --> 01:16:03,060
It's the nights
that are worse, eh?

1376
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:06,220
That's when all the fears
come creeping in.

1377
01:16:07,020 --> 01:16:09,060
I just wish
I could see
more progress.

1378
01:16:12,100 --> 01:16:13,190
[Sighing]

1379
01:16:14,090 --> 01:16:15,150
Come here, you.

1380
01:16:20,050 --> 01:16:23,080
They warned US it'd be
a slow process.

1381
01:16:25,040 --> 01:16:27,100
At least they haven't
used the word "aggressive."

1382
01:16:28,150 --> 01:16:31,020
You know it's bad
when they say that.

1383
01:16:31,060 --> 01:16:33,080
I haven't heard
that word.

1384
01:16:34,210 --> 01:16:38,090
If I die, it'll be a family
without a mother.

1385
01:16:39,020 --> 01:16:40,210
Lin, please don't.

1386
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:44,060
Sometimes it's so hard.

1387
01:16:45,210 --> 01:16:48,100
Sometimes I just
wanna give up.

1388
01:16:51,050 --> 01:16:52,150
Please.

1389
01:16:55,060 --> 01:16:56,150
Don't.

1390
01:17:04,230 --> 01:17:06,110
Your tests look fine.

1391
01:17:06,150 --> 01:17:08,070
No sign of cancer
in either breast.
Yeah?

1392
01:17:08,110 --> 01:17:11,070
It's gone.
So that trip in la
was worth it.

1393
01:17:11,110 --> 01:17:14,070
Well, I wish I could say
that but it's
too soon to tell.

1394
01:17:14,110 --> 01:17:16,060
The cancer's in remission,
not gone.

1395
01:17:16,100 --> 01:17:18,030
So far we can only
hope to contain it,

1396
01:17:18,070 --> 01:17:20,140
not cure it.
But it's good news.

1397
01:17:20,180 --> 01:17:22,100
Contain it?
For how long?

1398
01:17:22,140 --> 01:17:24,160
That's impossible to tell.

1399
01:17:24,200 --> 01:17:27,090
You'll need to be monitored
in London every
two weeks to make sure.

1400
01:17:27,130 --> 01:17:29,150
So I can do
whatever I want?

1401
01:17:29,190 --> 01:17:31,200
Quality of life
is essential.

1402
01:17:33,090 --> 01:17:34,110
[Sobbing]

1403
01:17:36,020 --> 01:17:37,070
Hey. Hey.

1404
01:17:39,110 --> 01:17:42,090
It's wonderful.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1405
01:17:43,200 --> 01:17:45,110
(Linda) Ok, hold that.

1406
01:17:46,090 --> 01:17:47,130
What do you think?

1407
01:17:47,170 --> 01:17:50,010
That could be a great
album cover, babe.

1408
01:17:53,050 --> 01:17:56,020
Mum, it says parsley.
Are you sure
you don't mean basil?

1409
01:17:56,060 --> 01:17:57,200
Hmm.

1410
01:18:00,180 --> 01:18:03,010
Oh. Oh, no.
You're right.

1411
01:18:03,050 --> 01:18:05,030
It-- it is basil.

1412
01:18:05,070 --> 01:18:08,060
Call the editor.

1413
01:18:08,100 --> 01:18:10,140
(Linda) I want to include
the flowers that I took

1414
01:18:10,180 --> 01:18:14,010
in the photo show,
and let's include
these ferns.

1415
01:18:14,050 --> 01:18:15,180
I took them
at kew garden.
Ok.

1416
01:18:15,220 --> 01:18:17,050
(Mary)
The florist is cool.

1417
01:18:17,090 --> 01:18:19,070
The invitations will be
ready Friday,

1418
01:18:19,110 --> 01:18:21,060
and Stella's working
on my dress.

1419
01:18:21,100 --> 01:18:23,020
Oh, I hope she has
something for me.

1420
01:18:23,060 --> 01:18:24,140
Nothing seems to fit,

1421
01:18:24,180 --> 01:18:27,050
and I've got her
Paris fashion show
coming up.

1422
01:18:27,090 --> 01:18:30,130
Mum, you're beautiful
as always.

1423
01:18:33,070 --> 01:18:35,020
(Paul) We can do that.

1424
01:18:35,060 --> 01:18:37,080
Of course, we can.

1425
01:18:37,120 --> 01:18:39,040
Yeah, but we'll have
to pick it up a bit
'cause the tide's coming in.

1426
01:18:39,080 --> 01:18:41,090
I want shells.
What?

1427
01:18:42,160 --> 01:18:45,080
It's shells,
it's shells you like.
Oh, Paul.

1428
01:18:47,160 --> 01:18:49,090
Oh, you like that,
do you?
Yeah.

1429
01:18:49,130 --> 01:18:51,050
Well, let's see.

1430
01:18:51,090 --> 01:18:53,070
Hang on.
There's more over there.

1431
01:18:54,050 --> 01:18:55,190
I'm sure there are.

1432
01:18:57,160 --> 01:18:59,090
[Seagulls cawing]

1433
01:19:08,210 --> 01:19:10,180
(Paul) Hey,
there's lots of 'em.

1434
01:19:10,220 --> 01:19:12,200
You have to wash
them though.

1435
01:19:13,000 --> 01:19:14,100
That's it, see?

1436
01:19:16,110 --> 01:19:18,150
Hey, are you all right,
darling?

1437
01:19:18,190 --> 01:19:19,220
Mmm-hmm.

1438
01:19:20,020 --> 01:19:21,200
What's up?
I just got so tired.

1439
01:19:22,000 --> 01:19:25,150
Oh, look. Come on. Come on.
Let's get you home.

1440
01:19:25,190 --> 01:19:27,210
You're all right.
Come on.

1441
01:19:29,090 --> 01:19:31,000
You'll be all right.
You'll be all right.

1442
01:19:31,040 --> 01:19:32,120
Come on. Let's go.

1443
01:19:34,100 --> 01:19:36,040
Here. Let me take that.

1444
01:19:41,180 --> 01:19:43,100
[Camera clicking]

1445
01:19:48,080 --> 01:19:50,010
Wonderful.

1446
01:19:51,010 --> 01:19:52,110
Thank you.

1447
01:19:56,020 --> 01:19:59,090
It's so peaceful here.
So beautiful.

1448
01:19:59,130 --> 01:20:02,020
How are your wedding plans
coming, darling?

1449
01:20:02,060 --> 01:20:04,060
Everything's going so well.

1450
01:20:07,160 --> 01:20:10,130
Mary,

1451
01:20:10,170 --> 01:20:13,080
do you think that
it might be possible
to move up the date?

1452
01:20:13,210 --> 01:20:14,210
Why, mum?

1453
01:20:15,010 --> 01:20:16,100
Because I wanna be there.

1454
01:20:17,210 --> 01:20:20,080
And things aren't
going well.

1455
01:20:20,120 --> 01:20:23,020
I talked to a doctor,
and it's in my liver.

1456
01:20:26,180 --> 01:20:28,140
Mary, will you
promise me something?

1457
01:20:30,220 --> 01:20:33,080
If anything should
happen to me,

1458
01:20:33,120 --> 01:20:35,140
will you take care
of your father?

1459
01:20:35,180 --> 01:20:37,110
Of course, I will.

1460
01:20:39,030 --> 01:20:40,140
We all will.

1461
01:20:54,180 --> 01:20:57,080
[People chattering]

1462
01:20:57,120 --> 01:21:01,160
To our lovely star,
Stella, whose
fashion's successful.

1463
01:21:01,200 --> 01:21:02,220
You liked it?

1464
01:21:03,020 --> 01:21:04,130
[Chuckling]
We loved it.

1465
01:21:05,140 --> 01:21:07,060
I am so proud of you.

1466
01:21:07,100 --> 01:21:09,180
Never in a million years
would I have thought

1467
01:21:09,220 --> 01:21:12,080
that I would produce
a Paris fashion whiz.

1468
01:21:12,120 --> 01:21:13,150
You either.

1469
01:21:13,190 --> 01:21:15,200
Oh, I don't know.
[Chuckling]

1470
01:21:16,000 --> 01:21:17,040
Brilliant.
Thank you.

1471
01:21:17,080 --> 01:21:18,070
(Woman)
Hello, again.

1472
01:21:18,110 --> 01:21:20,080
Hello.
Great show, Stella.

1473
01:21:20,120 --> 01:21:21,190
It was so good.
Thank you.

1474
01:21:21,230 --> 01:21:23,140
When did you replace
Karl lagerfeld?

1475
01:21:23,180 --> 01:21:24,180
(Both) November.

1476
01:21:24,220 --> 01:21:26,070
[All laughing]

1477
01:21:26,110 --> 01:21:27,170
Don't mind US.
Don't mind US.

1478
01:21:27,210 --> 01:21:29,050
We're just the silly,
proud parents.

1479
01:21:29,090 --> 01:21:30,170
Do you mind
if I steal her?

1480
01:21:30,210 --> 01:21:31,210
There some people
who really
wanna meet her.

1481
01:21:32,010 --> 01:21:33,080
Hey, she's all yours.

1482
01:21:33,120 --> 01:21:34,180
Come on.

1483
01:21:34,220 --> 01:21:36,040
Love you.

1484
01:21:37,110 --> 01:21:39,130
How about some
more champagne?

1485
01:21:45,010 --> 01:21:46,150
[Sighing]

1486
01:21:51,030 --> 01:21:53,110
You all right, mum?

1487
01:21:53,150 --> 01:21:56,200
Listen, if you're tired,
we can run you back
to the hotel, you know?

1488
01:22:03,230 --> 01:22:05,150
Where I really
wanna go

1489
01:22:07,150 --> 01:22:08,230
is Arizona.

1490
01:22:31,190 --> 01:22:33,080
[Birds chirping]

1491
01:22:48,130 --> 01:22:50,170
We're so lucky, Paul.

1492
01:22:50,210 --> 01:22:52,230
It's so beautiful here,

1493
01:22:53,030 --> 01:22:55,210
and it's been here
for hundreds of years,

1494
01:22:56,010 --> 01:22:58,170
and it will be here
long after we're gone.

1495
01:23:11,090 --> 01:23:13,030
(James)
You all right, dad?

1496
01:23:17,020 --> 01:23:18,180
Can I get you something?

1497
01:23:20,220 --> 01:23:23,050
No. No.
You get off to bed.

1498
01:23:33,160 --> 01:23:34,140
[Dog barking]

1499
